The paper discusses the integration of a generative neural network (Restricted Boltzmann Machines) into an Estimation of Distribution Algorithm for solving combinatorial optimization problems. This involves topics related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), data structures (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
